    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4557/23–25.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Riddle</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 45.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In compliance with the department’s cable
                    received June 2,<note n="a" xml:id="d357fna">Not printed.</note> I have this day
                    drawn upon you for $1,000, the proceeds of which, namely, rubles 1,940, I have
                    paid over to the Russian Red Cross Society, and have the honor to inclose
                    herewith the receipt of the Red Cross, with translation, together with a
                    memorandum of the banker showing the rate at which the above-named draft of
                    $1,000 was purchased.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. W. Riddle.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Receipt of the chief direction of the Russian Red Gross
                            Society.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 83890.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p rend="right">Rubles 1,940.</p>
                    <p>On May 21 (June 3), 1907, was received by the treasury of this administration
                        and credited under article No. 4199, from the American Red Cross Society for
                        the relief of famine sufferers, the sum of 1,940 rubles.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Tonko</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                        >Treasurer.</hi>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">I. Koshennikoff</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                        >Comptroller.</hi>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
